* phoenix as webfrontend based on elixir/erlang (MIT License)
* PostgreSQL as database backend (PostgreSQL License)
* PowerDNS as DNS server (GNU General Public License v2.0)
* PowerDNS dnsdist as DNS load balancer (GNU General Public License v2.0)

Add mnemonix – a unified interface to key/value stores (#4045)

Resolves #3240.

Chosen category: 

[Utilities](https://github.com/h4cc/awesome-elixir#utilities), as it is a tool meant to abstract away implementation details of key/value stores as to allow deferring the decision of the optimal one for later.

Other considered categories: 

- [caching](https://github.com/h4cc/awesome-elixir#caching)

    Didn't feel like the right fit, as it can be used for more than caching, although its most common use-case would be as a utility to abstract a cache store to experiment with other implementations down the line.

- [datastructures](https://github.com/h4cc/awesome-elixir#algorithms-and-data-structures)

    Didn't feel like the right fit, as it only wraps other data structure implementations to expose a key/value store interface.

- [interfaces](https://github.com/h4cc/awesome-elixir#behaviours-and-interfaces)

    Didn't feel like the right fit, as the current entries in the 'behaviours and interfaces' category are really just unimplemented behaviours. This is a pre-implemented interface. (Proposal: combine behaviours and protocol categories, split out interfaces? that seems like a better way to delineate these distinctions.)

Disclosure: I maintain [Mnemonix](https://github.com/christhekeele/mnemonix).

Bolt is a simple and fast web proxy living in the Erlang VM. Bolt can be used as a ssl proxy to prevent mixed content warnings on secure pages or to bypass CORS. For example as a SSL image proxy or for client side website scraping.
